The United States and Zambia have a strong relationship based on shared democratic values, growing commercial engagement, health cooperation, and people-to-people ties. The US praises Zambia's transparent and accountable governance and its role as the African co-host of President Biden's Second Summit for Democracy. The US Vice President's visit to Lusaka demonstrates the commitment to advancing cooperation with Zambia, including economic transformation, democracy and governance programming, global health efforts, and climate solutions. The US plans to provide over $505 million in bilateral assistance in fiscal year 2024. The Vice President will announce plans to strengthen commercial engagement, invest in democratic institutions and good governance, bolster health cooperation, and promote innovative food security, energy, and climate solutions during her visit.